Here we create a showdown extension that implements footnotes in a way that suits the SPA nature of the application.

[^alphanum] - indicates a note
[^alphanum]: Some Text Here - Indicates the refrerence text. 

Multiple notes can point to the same reference.

To use the plugin:

1. Activate Footnotes plugin in config.yaml
2. Run the build `npm run build`
3. Optionally, add `showdown_extensions: ['footnotes']` to config.yaml.
4. Add `showdown_extensions: ['footnotes']` to a markdown frontmatter.
5. Add `[^1]` note markers to a markdown text.
6. Add `[^1] Explanation text.` reference to the end of the markdown text.
7. Test the page.

